Buckeye Union High School District
May 16 at 5:53 AM ·

Good Morning Class of 2020!!!

We are so excited to see you all today at Phoenix Raceway to celebrate you! 🏁👨‍🎓👩‍🎓🏁

9:00 am Buckeye Union and Learning Center Graduates Check-In
10:00 am Parade Begins
11:30 am Parade Ends

12:00 pm Youngker and Learning Center Graduates Check-In
1:00 pm Parade Begins
2:30 pm Parade Ends

3:00 pm Estrella Foothills and Learning Center Graduates Check-In
4:00 pm Parade Begins
5:30 pm Parade Ends

Few things to remember:
📝Bring your signed waiver
▶Tune in to RADIO SIMULCAST ON FM CHANNEL 88.5 when you arrive
🚗Students and families must stay in vehicle at all times
🎥 We will be going "LIVE" on our District facebook page #BUHSD201 #buckeyeunionhighschooldistrict201
💧It's going to be warm...bring some water
📷 We will be taking graduate pictures from vehicle. Students can wear cap & gowns if they would like👨‍🎓
🎉Let's celebrate the Class of 2020

post_text: Update for Arizona schools on COVID-19 from Governor Doug Ducey and Superintendent of Public Instruction Kathy Hoffman.
shared_text:
Governor Doug Ducey is with Superintendent Kathy Hoffman and Arizona Department of Education.
March 15 at 4:14 PM ·

We’re joining together to keep Arizona’s kids, families, and school communities safe and healthy. Arizona is united, and we’ll get through this. Superintendent Kathy Hoffman

This decision is not made lightly, but it is the right thing to do to bring certainty and consistency to all Arizona schools. With schools closing, we are working together to provide assistance during this time and lessen the impact on all Arizona families.

It’s important for families & parents to know that while this will address operational issues, closing schools will not stop the spread of #COVID19. It is the recommendation of public health officials that kids who are not at school remain at home to the greatest extent possible.

For more information on ways to stay safe and healthy, visit http://azhealth.gov.

Read our full letter here: https://azgovernor.gov/governor/blog/2020/03/open-letter-arizona-families-educators-school-leaders-and-education-community

March 14, 2020

Dear BUHSD Community,

The Governing Board of the Buckeye Union High School District held an emergency Board Meeting at 2:00 P.M. today and approved the closure of the District’s schools until further notice. The District will continue to monitor the situation. As new information becomes available, we will update you. In the meantime, District staff will be finalizing strategies to continue instruction to students and the final plan will be communicated to parents and students as soon as it is available.

Sincerely,
Eric Godfrey
Superintendent

Congrats to the wolf of the week 1/21-1/25: Amanda Le

Amanda is one of the most dedicated and hard-working students I know. She always gives her best effort, completing her work with care and attention to detail. She prepares for class in advance to ensure that she gets the most out of instruction and is ready for any challenge. Additionally, Amanda exhibits excellent citizenship both in and out class, working well with others and helping others when possible. –Mrs. Kohli
